66529.title: Study for Petunias
66529.credit_line: Gift of Dr. Steven Conant in memory of Mrs. H. L. Conant
66529.provenance: Estate of the artist; Martin Diamond Fine Art, New York, New York; Gallery Schlesinger Limited, New York, New York; Janet Marqusee Fine Arts Ltd., New York, New York; Dr. Steven Conant, Indianapolis, Indiana (by purhcase); given to the Indianapolis Museum of Art in 2008.
66529.inscription: signed and dated in pencil., l.r.:  Blanche Lazzell 1928

extended_text.content:
The “Provincetown print,” with its flat planes of color and its collage-like layout, has a natural resemblance to Cubism, which contributed to the “modern” look of these prints.

While Study for Petunias is not unlike Lazzell’s preliminary drawings for her woodcuts, it is a study for a painting and therefore the Cubism is conscious, reflecting her study with Cubists Fernand Leger and Albert Gleizes in Paris in 1923–1924.
extended_text.title: Gallery Label
